article.headline: Dartmouth 67, Pennsylvania 49
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jeff Schiffner scored 15 points and Penn regained its shooting touch in the second half to defeat Dartmouth 67-49 Saturday night. Charlie Copp had 11 points and Jan Fikiel had 10 for Penn (9-8, 2-2 Ivy), which defeated the Big Green for the 14th straight time. Leon Pattman had 22 points for Dartmouth (3-17, 1-5), which dropped its ninth in a row. The Quakers held a 26-22 lead at halftime, despite making only 8-of-20 shots, including 2-of-8 from 3-point range. After the break, Tim Begley hit two 3-pointers during an 11-4 run, giving Penn a 37-26 advantage and touching off the team's 7-for-11 roll of 3-pointers in the second half. Dartmouth closed to 39-33, but three 3s by Schiffner, Copp and Eric Osmundson around two free throws by Pattman gave the Quakers a 48-35 with 10:49 to play. Dartmouth closed to 52-42 on a layup by David Gardner, but four straight free throws by Fikiel boosted the lead to 56-42 with six minutes remaining.
